---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Contact | adaviolationcalc.com';
const description = 'Contact the adaviolationcalc.com editorial team with corrections, feedback, or questions about ADA law and disability rights content.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Contact</h1>
  <p>For corrections, feedback, or questions about our content, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>. We read every message.</p>

  <h2>What we can help with</h2>
  <p>We welcome messages about factual inaccuracies, outdated legal citations, errors in calculator formulas, or suggestions for topics we should cover. If you find a case citation that has been reversed or a legal standard that has changed since our last update, let us know. We take accuracy seriously and update content promptly when errors are confirmed.</p>

  <h2>What we cannot help with</h2>
  <p>We cannot provide legal advice or respond to requests for case-specific analysis. Evaluating whether you have a viable ADA claim, whether your impairment qualifies as a disability, whether your employer was required to offer a specific accommodation, or what damages you might recover requires an attorney familiar with your specific facts and jurisdiction. For that, consult a licensed disability rights or employment attorney. Most handle ADA cases on contingency and offer free initial consultations.</p>
  <p>We also cannot respond to press inquiries, partnership requests, or solicitations for paid content placements. All editorial content is produced independently without commercial arrangements.</p>
</BaseLayout>
